    }

    // ...
};
```

For a singleton, remember that the destructor is only called once (since there is precisely one instance), and that's at the end of the application's runtime. So if your singletons are managing other dynamic resources, make sure they are properly cleaned up either in the destructor or via a controlled shutdown sequence.

